<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="fly-v">fly <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /flaɪ/    美 /flaɪ/  </p>
<p>(flew,flown)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>飞；飞翔；乘飞机 / 宇宙飞船：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Clumsy birds have to start flying early. 
笨鸟先飞。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I'm planning to <strong>fly to</strong> London next month.
我计划下个月乘飞机到伦敦。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>驾驶 (飞机等)；空运 (乘客、货物等)；飞越；放飞：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The pilot flies a new type of plane.
那位飞行员驾驶一架新型飞机。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>fly emergency medical supplies 
空运医疗急救物资</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>fly the English Channel 
飞越英吉利海峡</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>fly a kite</strong> 
放风筝</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>(使) 飘扬：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>fly the</strong> national <strong>flag</strong>
升国旗</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She stood in the wind with her hair flying.
她站在风中，头发随风飘动。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>飞跑；飞奔；(时间)飞逝：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She flew to meet her mother. 
她飞奔过去迎接母亲。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>Time flies</strong>. 
光阴似箭。</p></div>

<h4 id="5-flee">5.<strong>[正式用语] 逃走；逃离 (flee)；逃避：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Both suspects have flown the country.
两个嫌疑犯都已逃到国外。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The thief flew from justice. 
小偷逃避了审判。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="fly-off-the-handle">fly off the handle</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[非正式用语] 大发雷霆</strong>  </p>
<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>flying /'flaɪɪŋ/ n [U] <br />
flying /'flaɪɪŋ/ adj [只用于名词前]   </p></div>